



To Captain John Mercer. of the Virginia Regiment.
[Alexandria, 16 December 1755]



You are immediately, upon receipt hereof, to repair to Winchester, where you will meet with Colonel Washington, and receive further orders.
I am &c.

G:M. aid de camp.


Alexandria: December 16th 1755.
N:B. A Copy left at Alexandria, and another sent to Stafford, to him there.1

